# Testing discipline

- Property-test floors are spec, not tuning knobs: ≥1,000 Hypothesis examples per invariant
  (master doc §12.2) in the CI profile. Never lower `max_examples`, add `suppress_health_check`,
  or narrow strategies to make a failing property pass — a failing property is a finding.
- Never delete, skip, or xfail a failing test to unblock work. Fix the code or escalate.
  `xfail(strict=True)` with a linked issue is the only sanctioned deferral form.
- Property failures must reproduce from the printed seed/blob; `.hypothesis/` is never
  committed or cached.
- Integration tests run against a real Postgres with migrations applied from scratch each
  run; never against a reused/dumped database state. Migrations are plain SQL and
  language-neutral (ADR-0013 consequence).
- Test markers are load-bearing (`integration`, `fault_matrix`): adding or renaming one is a
  CI-design change — flag it, don't improvise.
- Fixtures must not embed real credentials or live-service responses; stub-destination
  fixtures are the norm (RFC-001 §10). Benchmark fixtures/holdout material never enter
  `tests/` (see benchmark-integrity rule).
